<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-10-28T14:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-10-28T14:45:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5103: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Munro</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-10-28T14:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                        1927—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7:45
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>301. President Diaz has asked the information, if possible by December
                            1st, regarding the chief points in the new electoral law to be proposed
                            by General McCoy in order that he may discuss the matter in his message
                            at the opening of Congress.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>